Text.Value: *The dawn greets you warmly, as if it knows of your victory. The Netherbrain is fallen, and the parasites have gone quiet.*
*How soon will your soul be snatched for the Hells' army?*
*Ulder Ravengard is fallen. The people will honour his son, saviour of Baldur's Gate, in raucous celebration.*
Descend to the Hells. Strike down each and every devil and demon you can.
*Your thoughts turn to Mizora. Will she stand in your way - and if so, will you dare resist?*
*When the tyrannised and the tormented cry out, you will listen. No one should suffer at the hands of man or monster.*
*Will your patron Mizora tarnish your legacy before the Hells snatch your soul?*
Train in the bow and the sword, now that Mizora's taken all your powers.
*With your father at your side, you've no doubts that you can restore the Council of Four and the Parliament of Peers.*
*Fiends will tremble at your sight as you tear your way through Avernus. You will take their horns and tails as your trophies.*
Help your father restore peace to Baldur's Gate.
*Under your watch, no demon will harm the people of the Sword Coast, and no wardevil will set it aflame.*
Organise a military parade and march the Flaming Fist through the streets.
*But you know there is work yet to be done. The people will be shaken, the city will hurt.*
Find Mizora, and make her pay for what she did to you.
*But still, you'll persevere. You won't aid them for the glory. You'll aid them because it's right.*
*They will call you a hero. And you'll march forth with pride, knowing you've earned the right.*
*She's dissolved your warlock skills, just as she promised. But Ansur has blessed you as the Heart of the Gate.*
Join the efforts to restore peace to Baldur's Gate.
*You will triumph with a sword in your hand and a bow at your back. You don't need the Hells' gifts to be mighty.*
Scout for devils and demons hiding on the Coast and destroy them.
Forget Avernus for now. Patrol the frontiers, seeking people to help.
*Your father is the most beloved man of all Baldur's Gate. He will honour his only son in raucous celebration.*
*You are the Heart of the Gate, a rightful Grand Duke. Your next step determines the leader you'll become.*
*Just as she promised, Mizora's dissolved your warlock skills. But you are confident nonetheless, for you embody the four pillars of power: Courage, insight, strategy, justice.*
*Going forth, you will prove you embody the four pillars of power: Courage, insight, strategy, justice.*
*She's dissolved your warlock skills, just as she promised. But you will triumph with a sword in your hand and a bow at your back.*

EditorData.logicalname: Did not get final Blade of Frontiers ending

Text.Value: Step out at your father's side. Proclaim your victory, and bask in the cheers.
*From there, you choose the road to follow. The Blade of Avernus, a man of his own making.*
*Mizora's dissolved your warlock skills, just as she promised. But you will triumph with a sword in your hand and a bow at your back.*
*But you know your work has just begun. Even now, you can feel the heat of the Hells. It is time for a culling.*
Consult Mizora. She can point the way to your first infernal victim.
*The people may not welcome you as a hero. They may see only a devil, frightening and despicable.*
The citizens need to grieve. Gather them, and mourn the fallen.
*Fiends will see the Blade of Avernus and tremble.*
*But you know your work has just begun. The people need a champion. They need the Blade of Frontiers.*
*From there, you choose the road to follow. The Blade of Frontiers, a man of his own making.*
Find Mizora, and make her pay for what she did to you.
*Then you can begin restoring the people's trust in their leaders.*
*Under your watch, no monster will harm the people of the Sword Coast.*
Approach the remaining patriars and dukes, and decide the best course of action.
*What will be your first act as Blade of Avernus?*
*You will bow your head for Grand Duke Stelmane. Your father, Ulder Ravengard. And all the victims of Gortash, Orin, and Ketheric, the Dead Three's chosen.*
*You descend from beloved stock. You've no doubts that you can restore the Council of Four and the Parliament of Peers.*
*For now, there's one thing you can be sure of: The Blade of Frontiers is a man of his own making.*
*What will the histories tell of Grand Duke Wyll Ravengard? Will you be called a man of mercy, or a tyrant? Will Baldur's Gate glow as a jewel, or be made a mockery?*
*You don't need the Hells' gifts to be mighty.*
*With her blessing, you will fell one fiend, then another. The disloyal will tremble at your sight as you tear your way through Avernus.*
*They may not welcome you as a hero. They may see only a devil, frightening and despicable.*
*How will you respond?*
*Avernus' powers still course through you. You will turn them against its own creatures.*
*You will track down the blasted devil. And you will tear her wings and cleave her infernal flesh until her screams are lost in the fires.*
*They'll gawk at your horns, at your infernal visage. But soon, they'll warmly welcome you as a Grand Duke.*
Hunt. Slay monsters and dangerous beasts before they can cause havoc.
*With all the important players in place, you'll present a united front to the people.*
Patrol the frontiers, seeking people to help.
*You'll fell great beasts and monsters. You'll be hailed as a hero. And you'll march forth with pride, knowing you've earned the right.*
*Like it or not, you are still chained to Mizora. You can't risk killing a devil whose loyalty is to her mistress, Zariel.*
Step forward with pride. Proclaim your victory, and bask in the cheers.
*Mizora's dissolved your warlock skills, just as she promised. But Ansur has blessed you as the Heart of the Gate.*
*If your city is to flourish, you must first cut out the tumours Gortash left behind.*
*A show of force will reveal you as a mighty commander, one who will keep order when enemies knock upon the gates.*
*The citizens of Baldur's Gate will welcome Ravengard's son with open arms.*
*They will call you a hero. And you'll always wonder if you've earned the right.*
*For now, you take a breath, sure of one thing over all others: You are a man of your own making.*
*You will bow your head for Grand Duke Stelmane - and the countless other victims of Gortash, Orin, and Ketheric, the Dead Three's chosen.*
*For now, you have no answers. But you do have a pledge:*
*Avernus' powers still course through you. You will continue to use them to help those who can't help themselves.*
*You take a deep breath, sure of one thing over all others: You are a man of your own making.*
*You will welcome all comers, regardless of ancestry or appearance. And you will dismiss any Flaming Fist who dares argue against it.*
*You'll fell great beasts and monsters. You'll be hailed as a hero. And you'll always wonder if you've earned the right.*
*The people will gawk at your horns, at your infernal visage. But soon, they'll warmly welcome you as a Grand Duke.*
*You embody the four pillars of power: Courage, insight, strategy, and justice.*
Open the gates to all refugees. Baldur's Gate will be sanctuary to all who need it.
*Your thoughts turn to your pact. Will Mizora ever stand in your way - and if so, will you dare resist?*
*Mizora treated you as a pet. She made your soul a mere plaything, and bid you choose between your father and your freedom.*

Synopsis: Wyll avatar reflects on his fate in the endgame.
